I'll start by fetching the API data using the network_fetcher tool. Since this is the first step in the workflow, I'll use the default URL parameter.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data"
}
</tool_call>

Now I need to parse the fetched data. Based on the workflow plan and tool dependencies, I'll use the data_processing_parser tool. Since the validator requires the parser, I'll execute this next.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json"
}
</tool_call>

I need to detect the format of the data fetched by network_fetcher. Since the parser and transformer tools require specific formats, I'll use the file_operations_scanner to inspect the data format.

<tool_call>file_operations_scanner
{
  "source": "data/input.json"
}
</tool_call>
